  "prompt": "Can you have sex, have a period, and still be pregnant?",
  "response": "Yes, it is possible to have sex and still be pregnant, but it is generally not possible to have a normal menstrual period if you are pregnant. However, some women may experience light bleeding or spotting during early pregnancy, which can sometimes be mistaken for a period. This is often referred to as implantation bleeding.\n\nIf you have had sex and are concerned about whether you are pregnant, the best way to determine this is to take a pregnancy test. If you have questions about your reproductive health, it is advisable to consult a healthcare professional for guidance.",
